Interested in purchasing BAIKALIKA tokens?

What is so great about this project?

By 2025, pure drinking water deficiency on earth will have grown up to 1.3-2.0 trillion cubic meters per year. China, Southeast Asia, Middle East and Africa will be the first to encounter fresh water severe shortage.

BAIKALIKA extracts the deep-layer water from the lake Baikal and works on promotionalpromotion of BAIKALIKA on most water-deficient regions in the world.

Thus, Baikalika project has a great potential for providing a stable supply of the pure drinking water to the consumers and also providing a great opportunity for the BAIKALIKA token holders to obtain substantial profits

What else do you need to know?

Experienced water producer

Baikalika already mines and sells the water from Baikal. The funding will be used to expand the scope of operations to supply token-holders.

Advanced technology

Blockchain solution for the BAIKALIKA tokens operations managed via smart contracts based on the proof of stake model guarantee transparency and safety for the BAIKALIKA tokens holders.

The token value set to grow

The buy-back program for the token holders assumes that the volume of the tokens operated at the market will decrease with the time thus impacting positively tokens’ price and liquidity.

How it works for the tokens-holders

Baikalika accumulates pure Baikal water on behalf of a token holder and delivers it to warehouse in China, Southeast Asia, Middle East or elsewhere.

Token holder

Token holder gets the following benefits:

  1. Personal water consumption
  2. Selling the water to a retail store

BAIKALIKA Token Sale

BAIKALIKA water is extracted three kilometers (about 1.6 miles) away from the shore, and from a 400-meter (about 0.22 miles) depth. This fresh drinking water is unaﬀected by human civilization, is unique in its purity, and has been acknowledged as etalon drinking water.

This water features the best combination of its properties: ﬂawless purity, high saturation with hydrogen and oxygen, no heavy metals present, and Ph in line with human blood.

Currently, Baikal is listed as UNESCO’s World Heritage, and is a world-known brand.

BAIKALIKA production is environmentally sound, which is confrmed by the relevant fndings and certifcates. From each recovered liter of the Baikal water, BAIKALIKA will be allocating a certain part of its proft into both non-governmental and governmental entities for preservation and developmental growth of the Baikal natural territory and the lake Baikal.

Project roadmap

Currently, the amount of the Baikal water produced by Baikalika plant is 8.5 million liters per year. The water in supplied to the Russian market.

The purpose of Crowdsale is fund raising for the plant output expansion and for the product introduction to water-deficient countries, in the first place –to China. In the long term, it is expected to increase volumes of supplied product and to enter the markets of South-Eastern Asia and Middle East.
